  "text": "We also checked whether CgAUX1 was sensitive to 1-NOA by attempting to disrupt the complementation of aux1 root gravitropism by CgAUX1. Treatment with 25 mM 1-NOA leads to a reversion to the mutant agravitropic phenotype (Fig. 4B) as in wild-type plants. This result indicates that CgAUX1, like AtAUX1 [CITATION_1] , is sensitive to the auxin influx inhibitor 1-NOA.",
